ts\neccentricity is excited to a high value and its orbit turns over by nearly 180\ndegrees, rolling over its major axis. This unusual behaviour, that is preserved\nwhen post-Newtonian terms are included in the numerical integrations, may also\nhelp understand the production of NEOs on retrograde orbits.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Oct 2014 09:52:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Nov 2014 07:21:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 6 Nov 2014 20:12:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-25"}
